<title>USA: LSB Industries completes loan pact.</title>
<headline>LSB Industries completes loan pact.</headline>
<dateline>OKLAHOMA CITY, Okla. 1997-02-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>LSB Industries Inc said Thursday it completed a $50-million, long-term loan agreement with John Hancock Mutual Life Insurance Co.</p>
<p>The company said the loan will be used to pay off existing mortgages of $20 million and for working capital. The loan is secured by certain fixed assets owned by the company's chemical business, LSB said.</p>
<p>LSB makes chemical products for the mining, agricultural and industrial markets.</p>
<p>Its shares were trading up 1/8 Thursday at 5.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk (312) 408-8787))</p>
